etymologies: late 17th century: from French, diminutive of Guillaume ‘William’

definitions: an auk (seabird) with a narrow pointed bill, typically nesting on cliff ledges.

notes.text: Family Alcidae, genus Cepphus: several species, in particular the North Atlantic black guillemot (C. grylle), with a white wing patch in summer and pale plumage in winter

shortDefinitions: auk seabird with narrow pointed bill
